Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It has been reported in Santa Cruz that the Special 
Antinarcotics Force has arrested more than 35 drug traffickers, 
most of them Colombians who operated in the outskirts of San 
Jose de Chiquitos. 
  The forces destroyed a laboratory that processed 450 kg of 
cocaine per week, and seized weapons including M-16 automatic 
rifles, shotguns, revolvers, and rifles. They are also 
confiscated automobiles and houses owned by the drug traffickers 
in the city of Santa Cruz. 
  It has also been reported that from 20 to 30 top Colombian 
drug traffickers linked to the Medellin and Cali cartels could 
be operating in Bolivia. They enter or leave Bolivia time after 
time as tourists going across the border with Brazil. 

